observations.recommendation:
We recommended that:
27. LCE executes Job Order contracts between the Municipality and the hired JOs, specifying therein: wage rate, work duration, functions/duties, and that there is no employer-employee relationship and that work rendered is not considered as government service;
28. The JO personnel submit approved DTRs, supported with authenticated copies of logbook printouts, and Accomplishment Reports certified correct by the officials who have direct supervision over their work, specifying in detail the work accomplishments for the particular period;
29. The HRMO/officials concerned/direct supervisors ensure that the hired JOs are faithfully reporting their log-in and log-out entries in their DTRs, and are performing their respective work assignment/duties, as indicated in their job order contracts; and
30. The Municipal Accountant ensures the completeness of supporting documents before claims are processed.
Fully Implemented

We recommend that the LCE should:

d. ensure that there is an Approved Budget for the SEF;

e. direct the Municipal Treasurer to maintain a separate depository
account for the SEF and regularly remit the SEF municipal share
thereof;

f. direct the Budget Officer to maintain a Registry for the SEF.
